Onne. VI.-11. cerdon. Cerdon was a native of Syria who went to Rome in the episcopata of Hyginus, s. 1). 157—141,and there, after several lapsas and reconciliations, separated from the Ohurch. He is known chiefly through his having been the toacher of Marciam and their fundamental tenete seem to have been identical. Iren. i. 24, iii. 4. 2 ; Hippol. Psilos. x. 155 Epiph.
